# Company data & research

Full detail: `.playbook/11_COMPANY_SCHEMA.md`, `.playbook/07_RESEARCH_GUIDE.md`, `archive/README.md`.

## Schema / publish bar

- Evidence over assumption; every claim needs a traceable source (employer > vendor > secondary > inference).
- Complete field pass on every new/refreshed row — no partial publish. Field table: `07_RESEARCH_GUIDE.md`.
- Public rows need non-empty `evidence` + `hiringEvidence` (http). AEM usage required.
- Set `verifiedAt` when evidence/hiring is checked. `ownerVerified: false` on agent-added/rewritten rows (only owner sets `true`).
- `hiringActive` = frequent cadence only, not “open now”; omit until evidenced. `ownerPreferred` only if owner marks it.
- Adobe stack only in `products` (short codes). `priority` via hiring-cadence rubric; BuiltWith-only cap 6 until Tier-1/2.
- `roles` = titles this employer uses. `signals` only with `source` + `asOf`.
- Live DB: `data/companies.json` only. Archive research is historical — re-verify before promoting. No duplicate ids.

## Research quality (hard)

1. **`careersUrl`** — employer-owned only (careers/ATS). Never job boards (Cutshort, Naukri, Indeed, LinkedIn `/jobs`, etc.).
2. Boards OK only in `hiringEvidence` / `jobSearchUrl`.
3. **M&A** — don’t add child brand if parent is listed; keep surviving row.
4. No careers page → don’t publish; park for owner review.
5. **`locations`** — hire countries + major hubs; don’t copy `hq`; not India-only for global SI/agency/GCC.
6. **`remote` / `noticePolicy` / `hiringActive` / `products`** — evidence only; never guess. Expand/remove product tags to match evidence.
7. **`notes`** — job-seeker facing only (no `DR-xxx` / agent jargon).

## After edits

`node scripts/verify-companies.js`; `npm run check-links` after batches; `npm run prerender` if counts/hero stats change.
